title: Hannibal
description: See how a gifted criminal profiler teams with cunning psychiatrist Hannibal Lecter to solve murders in this crime drama based on the characters from Thomas Harris' novels.

title: Chicago Fire
description: A drama series following the firefighters, paramedics and rescue squad of Chicago Firehouse 51.
genres: Derek Haas, Michael Brandt, Matt Olmstead, Joe Chappelle, Dick Wolf, Danielle Gelber, Peter Jankowski

title: Chicago P.D.
description: A 'Chicago Fire' spin-off following the men and women of the Chicago Police Department.
genres: Dick Wolf, Matt Olmstead, Michael Brandt, Derek Haas, Peter Jankowski, Danielle Gelber, Joe Chappelle

title: Chicago Med
description: Hospital dramas play out in a state-of-the-art trauma center in this "Chicago Fire" spin-off, which delves into the lives of its doctors, nurses and staff.

title: Femme Fatales
description: Anthology series about sexy, dangerous women.

title: Friday Night Dinner
description: The quirky experiences of a family when they get together for dinner every Friday night.
premiere: Kenton Allen, Nira Park, Caroline Leddy

title: Friday Night Lights
description: Creator Peter Berg's drama centering on the players and coach of a high-school football team in Dillon, Texas, a small town in which football is near religion. The critically acclaimed series is based on the best-selling book and 2004 film of the same name.
genres: Peter Berg, Brian Grazer, David Nevins, Jason Katims, Sarah Aubrey, Jeffrey Reiner, David Hudgins, John Cameron

title: Autopsy: The Last Hours Of...
description: Celebrity autopsy results are combined with the revelations of the late stars' friends and families to offer a comprehensive overview of the events leading up to the icons' untimely deaths.

title: Madam Secretary
description: This drama follows the professional and personal life of Secretary of State Elizabeth McCord, a brilliant CIA analyst-turned-college professor who returns to Washington, D.C., as a favor to the president, whom she considers a friend. While he values Elizabeth's frankness and how she confidently handles the job on her own terms, those qualities aren't always appreciated, especially by other members of the White House staff.

cast.character: Diplomatic Security Head Agent Fred Cole
